[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer security sanitizer has detected an OS command injection vulnerability [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduring fuzz testing. The crash trace shows that untrusted data reaches a call to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Runtime.exec` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia `ProcessBuilder.start`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in Apache Tika’s `ExternalParser`. The [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39missue was flagged as `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: OS Command Injection`, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating potential for remote code execution when attacker-controlled input is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mused in OS command invocations.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- What the issue is  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  During a fuzzing session, Jazzer’s `OsCommandInjection` sanitizer intercepted a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall to `ProcessBuilder.start` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand underlying `Runtime.exec`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m originating from [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mApache Tika’s `ExternalParser`. This indicates that input supplied to the parser [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcan influence the construction of an OS command, leading to possible injection of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marbitrary commands.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The issue is classified as OS Command Injection: executing OS commands or [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvoking external programs using data that can be manipulated by an attacker.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Important observations and findings  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The sanitizer stack trace pinpoints the hook in [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`OsCommandInjection.processImplStartHook` as the guard that detected the risky [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Calls to `ProcessBuilder.start` occur in `ExternalParser.parse`, which is used [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby Tika to hand off certain parsing tasks to external applications.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer entry point is provided by `com.example.HtmlParserFuzzer`, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspecifically methods `fuzzerTestOneInput` and `parseOne`. These methods feed [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marbitrary HTML or embedded content into Tika’s parser chain.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The parser chain involves several components: `ParserDecorator`, [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`CompositeParser`, `AutoDetectParser`, and `DelegatingParser`, before reaching [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ExternalParser`.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The crash input [0m[1;39m([0m[39ma malformed or malicious document[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m triggers the vulnerable [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode path, resulting in the Jazzer security violation.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code areas to investigate  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. **ExternalParser.parse [0m[1;39m([0m[39mExternalParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:274[0m[39m & [0m[1;36m314[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** – review how [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcommand-line arguments are constructed and whether untrusted input is passed [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectly to the OS command.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. **HTML-related handlers** [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`HtmlHandler`, `JSoupParser`, [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`XHTMLDowngradeHandler`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m – understand how embedded data URIs or HTML elements may [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcarry payloads that influence external parsing calls.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. **Fuzzer harness** [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`HtmlParserFuzzer.parseOne`, `fuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m – [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malthough not the root cause, it shows how inputs are delivered to Tika and may help[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreproduce the issue.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. **OSCommandInjection sanitizer hook** [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`OsCommandInjection.jav[0m[1;92ma:63[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m – [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfirms the exact API invocations flagged as unsafe. Reviewing this can clarify [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe precise parameters passed to the command and their origin.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCollectively, these components form the execution path from user-supplied data to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mOS command execution. A thorough code review in these areas will provide a holistic[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderstanding of how untrusted input leads to the detected command injection.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Prevent untrusted metadata values from being used verbatim as OS commands.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In [0m[1;35mHtmlHandler.configureExifTool[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, validate the `path` before [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpassing it to ExternalParser.setCommand.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Implement a helper method `[0m[1;35misValidExecutablePath[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that returns[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`true` only if:  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • `path` is non-null, non-empty, contains no whitespace or shell [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetacharacters [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `;|&<>``[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • `new [0m[1;35mFile[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.isFile[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mcanExecute[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` both return `true`  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In `configureExifTool`, before `[0m[1;35mexifToolParser.setCommand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath, [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"$[0m[32m{[0m[32mIN[0m[1;33mPUT[0m[32m}[0m[32m"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, add:  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35misValidExecutablePath[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Ignored invalid exiftool path override via metadata: [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m"[0m[39m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return retVal;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m skip override, preserve existing behavior[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - This ensures only safe, on-disk executables can be used, blocking attempts [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto inject flags or shell code.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Always invoke external processes via the argument-array API [0m[1;39m([0m[39mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstead of mixing `[0m[1;35mRuntime.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mRuntime.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In [0m[1;35mExternalParser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaInputStream…, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Replace the block at lines [0m[1;36m311[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m316[0m[39m:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd.length == [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            process = [0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            process = [0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        with:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        process = new [0m[1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                    [0m[1;35m.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Import `java.lang.ProcessBuilder` as needed.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. This change removes the single-string fallback, ensuring Java does not [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mperform any internal string parsing or tokenization that might reintroduce [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minjection vectors, and uses a well-defined exec-array approach.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Keep existing functionality intact.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The new `isValidExecutablePath` method and its check only guard metadata [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverrides; default parser behavior [0m[1;39m([0m[39musing bundled/external defaults from [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfiguration[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remains unchanged.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Switching to `[0m[1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` does not change how arguments are passed to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe executable; it merely uses the safer array‐based API. Existing tests and [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mharnesses that rely on default parsers will still function normally.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Potential side effects and mitigation.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Commands that legitimately require a path with spaces will now be rejected. If[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis use case is expected, users must wrap such paths in quotes in the overall Tika[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfiguration [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnot via metadata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or supply a metadata value without spaces [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvia configuration files rather than inline HTML[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If any tests rely on overriding exiftool via metadata for integration testing,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupdate those tests to use a valid, no-space path or mock the executable location.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Why this approach?  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validating the metadata‐supplied path blocks the root cause: untrusted input [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreaching `Runtime.exec`.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Using `ProcessBuilder` exclusively eliminates the risk introduced by [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mRuntime.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and aligns with best practices for external process [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvocation in Java.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Both fixes are localized to the core parser classes and do not touch harness, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing, or test code, preserving existing behavior and test coverage.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo external libraries or harness code are modified; all changes are confined to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ExternalParser` and the HTML module’s `configureExifTool` method. [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m[12/25/25 20:12:01][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.EVALUATE -> TeamStatus.ANALYZE                  ]8;id=395595;file:///home/qqor/aixcc/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=915961;file:///home/qqor/aixcc/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35morg.apache.tika.parser.CompositeParser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCompositeParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:298[0m[1;39m)[0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35mcom.example.HtmlParserFuzzer.parseOne[0m[1;39m([0m[39mHtmlParserFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:69[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.HtmlParserFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[39mHtmlParserFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:40[0m[1;39m)[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: 3c99eeb1380e104c[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer observed an OS command injection in Apache Tika’s `ExternalParser`, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhere unvalidated command arguments passed to `Runtime.exec` could be controlled by[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man attacker. The submitted patch replaced all `Runtime.exec` calls with a [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` invocation and added a new `isValidExecutablePath` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguard in `HtmlHandler` to reject suspicious executable paths before configuring [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExifTool. After applying the patch, the build failed in the HTML parser module with[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma compilation error: `cannot find symbol: variable LOG` in `HtmlHandler.java`.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A Jazzer security hook reported `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: OS Command [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInjection` at the call site in `ExternalParser.processImplStartHook`.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack trace shows uncontrolled data flowing into [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The vulnerability surface is in `ExternalParser` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwithin `tika-core`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and is [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexercised via the HTML parser [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`HtmlParserFuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which delegates to [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mExternalParser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations from the Issue  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Two overloads of `Runtime.exec` are invoked based on command-array length.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The offending code resides in [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/external/ExternalParser.java`.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The HTML handler [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`HtmlHandler`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m allows users to override the path to ExifTool[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvia metadata without validation.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `ExternalParser.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m308[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the two `Runtime.exec` branches [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwere removed and replaced with:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     process = new [0m[1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   [0m[1;35m.redirectErrorStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfalse[0m[1;39m)[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   [0m[1;35m.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `HtmlHandler.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m383[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, a private helper [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35misValidExecutablePath[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` was added, which rejects null, empty, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhitespace- or shell-special-char-containing strings, and verifies that the file [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexists and is executable.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Before calling `[0m[1;35mexifToolParser.setCommand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath, [0m[32m"$[0m[32m{[0m[32mIN[0m[1;33mPUT[0m[32m}[0m[32m"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`, the handler now[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoes:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35misValidExecutablePath[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Ignored invalid exiftool path override via metadata: [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m"[0m[39m, path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return retVal;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Compilation failed in the HTML parser module with:[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     cannot find symbol: variable LOG[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     location: class org.apache.tika.parser.html.HtmlHandler[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This indicates that `HtmlHandler` either does not declare a `LOG` logger [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstance or the patch did not add the necessary import or field.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Further Investigation  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify the declaration of a logger in `HtmlHandler`. Other Tika handler [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclasses typically have a line such as:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     private static final Logger LOG = [0m[1;35mLoggerFactory.getLogger[0m[1;39m([0m[39mHtmlHandler.class[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     or use `org.slf4j.Logger`.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Check for missing imports [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`import org.slf4j.Logger; import [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morg.slf4j.LoggerFactory;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and reconcile with Tika’s logging conventions.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Audit other parser modules to ensure that the new `isValidExecutablePath` or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msimilar guards, if applied elsewhere, also reference a valid `LOG` instance.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm that the `ExternalParser` changes propagate correctly to all callers [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand that no remaining uses of `Runtime.exec` exist.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m421[0m[39m:            Map<MediaType, Parser> parsers = [0m[1;35mexParser.getParsers[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m422[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mparsers.remove[0m[1;39m([0m[39mJPEG[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m423[0m[39m:            return;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m424[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m425[0m[39m:        ExternalParser exifToolParser = [0m[1;35mgetExistingExifToolParser[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m426[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexifToolParser == null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m428[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m429[0m[39m:        Set<MediaType> supported = new [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHashSet<>[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mexifToolParser.getSupportedTypes[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-html-m[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39module/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/html/HtmlHandler.jav[0m[1;92ma:17[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m25[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m17[0m[39m:package org.apache.tika.parser.html;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m18[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m19[0m[39m:import java.io.IOException;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m20[0m[39m:import java.net.MalformedURLException;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m21[0m[39m:import java.net.URL;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m22[0m[39m:import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;[0m                                        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-html-m[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39module/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/html/HtmlHandler.jav[0m[1;92ma:26[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m30[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m26[0m[39m:import java.util.List;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m27[0m[39m:import java.util.Locale;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m28[0m[39m:import java.util.Map;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m29[0m[39m:import java.util.Set;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m:import java.util.regex.Matcher;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Reapply and retain the `ExternalParser` changes from the last patch:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove the two `[0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` branches.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replace with a single `new [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.redirectErrorStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfalse[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` invocation.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This preserves the mitigation for OS-command-injection while keeping existing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogging in `ExternalParser`.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. In `HtmlHandler.java`, introduce the SLF4J logger so that `[0m[1;35mLOG.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompiles:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Add the SLF4J imports immediately after the existing `java.*` and `javax.*` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimports:[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      import org.slf4j.Logger;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Declare the logger field at the top of the class [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., right after `public [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclass HtmlHandler [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      private static final Logger LOG = [0m[1;35mLoggerFactory.getLogger[0m[1;39m([0m[39mHtmlHandler.class[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Ensure the previously added `[0m[1;35misValidExecutablePath[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` guard and its [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall‐site in `configureExifTool` remain unchanged. This guard blocks invalid or [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minjectable paths before passing them to `ExternalParser`.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Perform a quick audit for any remaining `Runtime.exec` calls elsewhere in the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase; all should now use `ProcessBuilder` or otherwise be validated.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Rebuild and run existing unit and integration tests to confirm:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No regressions in HTML parsing.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No new compilation errors.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The compilation failure was solely due to the missing `LOG` symbol in [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`HtmlHandler`. Adding the standard SLF4J imports and logger field aligns with [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting conventions in Tika [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ExternalParser` and other handlers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- We preserve the new security logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`isValidExecutablePath`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the improved [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocess‐launch mechanism in `ExternalParser`.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No harness, fuzzing, or test code is modified, so existing tests and fuzzers [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremain unaffected.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This approach addresses the compilation error and ensures the original [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mOS-command-injection fix remains intact.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer fuzzing run against Apache Tika’s HTML parser triggered a [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFuzzerSecurityIssueCritical for OS command injection. The stack trace indicates [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat `ExternalParser` calls `[0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattacker-controlled input. A patch was proposed to harden command execution by [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mswitching to `ProcessBuilder` in `ExternalParser` and adding an [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`isValidExecutablePath` check plus logging in `HtmlHandler`. After applying the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch, the HTML parser module fails to compile with dozens of “illegal start of [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtype” and “<identifier> expected” errors in `HtmlHandler.java`.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A Jazzer security sanitizer raised `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: OS Command [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInjection` when the fuzzer fed crafted HTML into Tika.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack trace shows the vulnerability arises in `ExternalParser.parse`, where [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcommands are executed via `[0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` without sanitization.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The issue highlights that attacker-controlled data reaches OS command execution [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethods, potentially leading to remote code execution.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. In `ExternalParser.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m308[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Removed the `[0m[1;35mRuntime.getRuntime[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.exec[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` calls for single-string and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstring-array overloads.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replaced them with a single `new [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mProcessBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmd[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.redirectErrorStream[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfalse[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` invocation.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. In `HtmlHandler.java`:  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Imported SLF4J’s `Logger` and `LoggerFactory`.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Declared a `private static final Logger LOG` at class scope.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added a helper method `[0m[1;35misValidExecutablePath[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that rejects null, empty[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnames or paths containing shell metacharacters, and ensures the file is executable.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `[0m[1;35mconfigureExifTool[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, inserted a guard that logs and returns [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mearly if `path` fails validation.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Left the existing `[0m[1;35msetCommand[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath, [0m[32m"$[0m[32m{[0m[32mIN[0m[1;33mPUT[0m[32m}[0m[32m"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call in place for valid [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The build fails in the HTML parser module with ~[0m[1;36m40[0m[39m compilation errors in [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`HtmlHandler.java`, all pointing to “illegal start of type” and “<identifier> [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpected” around the newly inserted code.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A final error notes “reached end of file while parsing,” indicating a likely [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmismatched brace or code inserted outside the proper class body.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The import and class declaration region of `HtmlHandler.java` where SLF4J imports[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand `public class HtmlHandler` were added—verify that the patch did not [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maccidentally duplicate the class declaration or disrupt existing structure.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The placement of the `isValidExecutablePath` method and `LOG` field to ensure [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthey reside inside the `HtmlHandler` class and not at the top level.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Bracing and indentation around the edited sections to confirm no missing or extra[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcurly braces.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The original `ExternalParser` changes to verify compatibility with existing [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merror-handling and resource-management patterns.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Build configuration or IDE settings that might influence parsing of the modified [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfiles.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
